<ul>
<li>Users are able to flag suspicious answers they encounter while browsing. Similarly, sometimes researchers do not feel confident in their interpretation of answers that they’re adding and flag the answer for review. These answers can be verified or fixed by other users.</li>
<li>By checking and potentially fixing these answers you can help us to improve the data quality on wiki rate and in turn its usage and impact. </li>
<li>There is an indication that the answer might be wrong. By checking it you can help us resolve the suspicion and improve the data quality.</li>
</ul>